9:
When you have attained wisdom, it will be like a beautiful wreath of honor on your head;
\q2 she will give you a beautiful crown."
\q1

14:
Do not do what wicked people do, nor be with them;
\q1 do not be with people who do evil things. 
\q1

15:
Stay far from those ways;
\q2 turn another way and go on another road. 
\q1

17:
They get their strength, and they are fed by doing what is wrong;
\q and they are intoxicated by hurting others; they get drunk on it.
\q1

23:
Protect your heart with all your strength and guard what you love;
\q2 guard it, for it becomes a fountain overflowing with life. 
\q1

24:
Make it your aim to keep any lying speech, any deceptive talk away from you; 
\q2 and put away from you anything that might corrode their values or harm them with useless talk. 
\q1

26:
Take care about where you will go, and take care to be sure that the way is safe;
\q2 then you will know what to expect along the way.
\q1
